WEBVTT

00:00:00.190 --> 00:00:04.300
Before going further, let’s briefly review the sampling capabilities available

00:00:04.300 --> 00:00:05.800
in PyAnalySeries.

00:00:06.890 --> 00:00:09.680
The application allows you to redefine the sampling of your

00:00:09.680 --> 00:00:12.120
series in a flexible and controlled way.

00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:16.650
You can resample a dataset either using a regular step

00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:19.080
or based on the X-values of another series.

00:00:20.270 --> 00:00:23.680
An integration option is also available, allowing values to be

00:00:23.680 --> 00:00:25.110
averaged over intervals.

00:00:26.410 --> 00:00:30.030
Several interpolation methods are available, depending on the nature of

00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:32.760
your data and the level of precision required.

00:00:33.940 --> 00:00:38.290
These tools help standardize your datasets, make comparisons more robust

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:41.900
and prepare the data for further analysis or visualization.

00:00:43.010 --> 00:00:44.930
Let’s now look at a concrete example.

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:48.820
We now focus on the record called “ PercAndes ”,

00:00:48.820 --> 00:00:52.590
which reflects the relative contribution of Andean versus lowland input

00:00:52.830 --> 00:00:56.350
from Amazonian terrigenous sediments deposited at the core site.

00:00:57.520 --> 00:01:01.810
The record exhibits uneven temporal resolution over time, due to

00:01:01.810 --> 00:01:04.300
a reduced sedimentation rate in the lower part of the

00:01:04.300 --> 00:01:04.940
record.

00:01:06.180 --> 00:01:09.280
To address this issue, we resample the record using a

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:10.560
regular step size.

00:01:11.710 --> 00:01:15.240
Select the series, then go to Process → Define Sampling

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:19.630
Define the sampling parameters.

00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:24.980
For example, resample the record every 2 5 0 years

00:01:25.090 --> 00:01:26.200
by entering 0.

00:01:26.200 --> 00:01:29.080
2 5 in the sampling step field.

00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:32.540
The record now has a regular spacing of 0.

00:01:32.540 --> 00:01:33.820
2 5 kyr.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:37.990
You can then save both the sampling configuration and the

00:01:37.990 --> 00:01:39.350
resampled series.

00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:43.330
Let’s now inspect the resampled series.
